--- !u!114 &610992841
MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 610992839}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: f4688fdb7df04437aeb418b961361dc5, type: 3}
  m_Name: 
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Unity.TextMeshPro::TMPro.TextMeshProUGUI
  m_Material: {fileID: 0}
  m_Color: {r: 1, g: 1, b: 1, a: 1}
  m_RaycastTarget: 1
  m_RaycastPadding: {x: 0, y: 0, z: 0, w: 0}
  m_Maskable: 1
  m_OnCullStateChanged:
    m_PersistentCalls:
      m_Calls: []
  m_text: 'v0.1.1

    This is a very basic and rough prototype of Rodent Problem
    just to start getting feedback and see if this is something I actually want to
    work on


    The general idea of the game is it is a dungeon crawler where you
    play as a sleazy netizen taking his rodent infestation into his own hands. You
    will eventually progress through multiple (randomly generated) levels into Rattopia,
    defeating waves of rats and boss enemies to kill the Rat King.


    This prototype
    is nothing near that and has 1 premade level, no art, one type of enemy, and
    two weapons. And it''s buggy.


    I''m getting feedback on nearly every part
    of this idea, including music and general vibes. Try going into settings to change
    which music track plays to help me decide which vibe is best for the game. And
    please give me any feedback you think of : ) (even if its that the game is garbage
    and I shouldn''t waste my time on it)


    Known Issues:

    - Visible bullet
    trail sometimes doesn''t feel like it matches where you click, but hit registration
    should work

    - Occasionally the rats will not attack you even though they
    are in range. Restarting should fix this.'
